-- First-Half Profit for China-Listed Companies Rises 50%, Securities Reports
-- Bloomberg News
-- 2010-08-01T23:34:53Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-08-01/first-half-profit-for-china-listed-companies-rises-50-securities-reports.html

          
          
             China-listed companies posted a 50
percent gain in net income in the first half, the Shanghai
Securities News reported, citing 264 companies that have
released earnings results as of July 31.  
          
          


  
     
       
     
           
                           
                 
                 
                                       
                                   
               
                        
           
                          Aug. 2 (Bloomberg) -- Sean Darby, chief Asian equity strategist at Nomura Holdings Inc. in Hong Kong, speaks with Bloomberg's Rishaad Salamat about China's stock market and economy.
